    </div>
    
    <div id="tabs">
      <span>overview</span>
      <a href="http://www.libgosu.org/cgi-bin/mwf/forum.pl">forum</a>
      <a href="http://github.com/jlnr/gosu/wiki/">documentation</a>
      <a href="http://www.libgosu.org/rdoc/">ruby reference</a>
      <a href="http://www.libgosu.org/cpp/">c++ reference</a>
    </div>

    <p>
      Gosu is a <strong>2D game development library</strong> for the Ruby and C++ programming languages, available for <strong>Mac OS X, Windows and Linux</strong>. It has been in development since <b>2001</b>. The C++ version is also available for <strong>iPad, iPhone and iPod&nbsp;Touch</strong>.<br>
      <small>Visual&nbsp;C++&nbsp;2008 (recommended) or 2010 required for the Windows C++ version, but the free Express versions are fine.</small>
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Both languages have access to:
      <ul>
        <li> 2D graphics and text, accelerated by 3D hardware</li>
        <li> Sound samples and music in various formats</li>
        <li> Keyboard, mouse and gamepad input</li>
      </ul>
    
      Ruby/Gosu integrates well:
      <ul>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>gosu</strong></tt><br>complete with examples, precompiled for Windows &amp; OS&nbsp;X</li>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>texplay</strong></tt><br><a href="http://www.libgosu.org/cgi-bin/mwf/topic_show.pl?tid=79">pixel-based drawing</a> on Gosu images, by <a href="http://github.com/banister">banister</a></li>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>chingu</strong></tt><br><a href="https://github.com/ippa/chingu">a library that adds more game logic</a>, by <a href="http://github.com/ippa">ippa</a></li>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>ruby-opengl</strong></tt><br>the <a href="http://ruby-opengl.rubyforge.org/">standard Ruby OpenGL gem</a> works fine with Gosu to add 3D effects<br><small>(See the included example, or <a href="http://github.com/tjbladez/gosu-opengl-tutorials">this fine bundle of tutorials by tjbladez</a>. Also note <a href="http://www.libgosu.org/cgi-bin/mwf/topic_show.pl?tid=278">this thread</a> if you have problems installing on Windows)</small></li>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>chipmunk</strong></tt><br>a <a href="http://wiki.slembcke.net/main/published/Chipmunk">popular physics library</a> with an <a href="http://github.com/jlnr/gosu/wiki/Ruby-Chipmunk-Integration">integration example in the wiki</a>
        <li class="gem"> <tt>gem install <strong>rmagick</strong></tt><br>can be used as a more powerful but harder-to-distribute alternative to TexPlay, example included in Gosu
      </ul>
    </p>
    
